<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-24T15:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-24T15:36:00-05:00" n="1072" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1072">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/3778.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Canada</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Vera Cruz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-24T14:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 24, 1914, 2 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Now advised by Admiral Badger plan send war vessel to Frontera and other
                            places not feasible owing possible incitement Mexicans <pb facs="0791" n="675" xml:id="pg_675"/> against Americans. The Admiral is prepared
                            when authorized and strongly recommends that such authorization be given
                            to charter a steamer here to be sent immediately for these refugees who
                            will be taken care of here on arrival. Please rush reply. Steamer can
                            probably be secured for three to four hundred dollars gold a day
                            exclusive of provisions and coal.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Canada</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>